<doc id="561551" wikidata="Q5575712" url="?curid=561551" title="Voice of an Angel">
<text>Voice of an Angel is the debut studio album by then-12-year-old soprano Charlotte Church, released in 1998. The Sony Music recording was extremely popular, selling millions of copies, and made Church the youngest artist in history with a number 1 album on the British classical crossover charts. The album is a collection of arias, sacred songs and traditional pieces.

==Track listing==
Note: Sian Edwards conducted the Orchestra and Chorus of Welsh National Opera, with Meinir Huelyn on harp.

